=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Protect 3-aminopiperidine on the exocyclic NH with Boc2O to give tert-butyl(piperidin-3-yl)carbamate, then acylate the ring N with 2,4-dichlorobenzyl chloroformate to form tert-butyl 1-(((2,4-dichlorobenzyl)oxy)carbonyl)piperidin-3-ylcarbamate | Step 2: Remove Boc with TFA to obtain 1-(((2,4-dichlorobenzyl)oxy)carbonyl)piperidin-3-amine | Step 3: Build the acid fragment by Cu-catalyzed azide–alkyne cycloaddition of methyl 5-hexynoate with NaN3 (or TMSN3) to give the triazole ester methyl 4-(1H-1,2,3-triazol-4-yl)butanoate, then saponify to 4-(1H-1,2,3-triazol-4-yl)butanoic acid, i.e. HOOC-CCCc1c[nH]nn1 | Step 4: Couple 4-(1H-1,2,3-triazol-4-yl)butanoic acid with 1-(((2,4-dichlorobenzyl)oxy)carbonyl)piperidin-3-amine (HATU/DIPEA or EDCI) to give O=C(CCCc1c[nH]nn1)NC1CCN(C(=O)OCc2cc(Cl)cc(Cl)c2)CC1.

